# üéôÔ∏è OpenMeet

Open-source macOS menu bar app for real-time meeting transcription and AI-powered summaries.

## Features

- üé§ Real-time transcription during meetings
- üìù Automatic meeting summaries with action items
- üîí 100% local processing (privacy-first)
- üÜì Completely free and open source
- ‚ö° Works with Zoom, Google Meet, Teams, Slack

## Tech Stack

- **Language:** Python 3.10+
- **Speech-to-Text:** Whisper.cpp (local, C++)
- **Summarization:** llama-cpp-python (local LLM with GGUF models)
- **UI:** Rumps (menu bar) + Tkinter (windows)
- **Audio Capture:** PyAudio + SoundDevice
- **Diarization:** Pyannote.audio (optional speaker identification)

## Status

‚úÖ **Functional** - Core transcription and summarization working, PyInstaller and py2app bundling ready

## Installation

### Prerequisites
- **macOS 12.0+**, **Windows 10+**, or **Linux** (Ubuntu 18.04+)
- Python 3.10+
- 8GB RAM minimum (16GB recommended)
- C/C++ compiler (for building whisper.cpp)

### Quick Setup
```bash
# Clone repository
git clone https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/openmeet.git
cd openmeet

# Run setup script
./setup.sh
```

## Manual Setup

### 1. Clone and environment
```bash
git clone https://github.com/ggerganov/whisper.cpp.git
cd openmeet
python3 -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate  # On Windows: venv\Scripts\activate
```

### 2. Install Python dependencies
```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

### 3. Build Whisper.cpp
```bash
cd whisper.cpp
mkdir build && cd build
cmake ..
cmake --build . --config Release
cd ..

# Download base model (or other sizes: tiny, small, medium, large)
bash ./models/download-ggml-model.sh base
cd ..
```

### Development (from source)
```bash
source venv/bin/activate  # On Windows: venv\Scripts\activate
python src/app.py
```

### Packaged App

#### macOS (PyInstaller)
```bash
./build.sh
open dist/OpenMeet.app
```

